Class CoordinatePolarMathematical

    I_Unitable<CoordinatePolarMathematical>, java.lang.Comparable<CoordinatePolarMathematical>
    public class CoordinatePolarMathematical
extends A_CoordinatePolar<CoordinatePolarMathematical,​AngleMathematical>
    Defines the basic elements of arbitrary two-dimensional polar coordinate system based on mathematical angles. Creates a Cartesian coordinate from this polar coordinate with an explicit origin. For convenience, the Cartesian coordinate system is defined for Java graphics, with (0,0) in the top-left corner.
